								<title xml:lang="en">Numbers</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="282r" to="344r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Deuteronomy</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="344r" to="346v"/>
								<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tefilah</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="346v" to="357v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Additional comments on the Pentateuch</title>
								<filiation>Cf. <ref target="Neubauer_1891" type="number">2253/12</ref>
								</filiation>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent rend="visible">357 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>325</height>
										<width>225</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>200</height>
										<width>135</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>357 folios (+ 2 unfoliated flyleaves at the beginning and 5 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>27 quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
									<p>Catchwords at the end of the quires (sometimes cut away), with Hebrew letters as signatures written partly over and partly under the respective catchword.</p>
									<p>The Hebrew signatures are omitted in the latter portion of the manuscript.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>A leaf is missing after folio 8.</p>
									<p>Some signs of worming.</p>
									<p>Ink fading on several pages.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="32" writtenLines="32">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling is visible. Writing depends from the ruled line.</p>
									<p>Many marginal corrections and additions, also with some variant readings in the margins.</p>
									<p>Many clauses have been effaced.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Fine Italian semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of the 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Note of former owners, folio 1r. The manuscript once belonged to the Norzi family.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Domenico Irosolimitano</name>, Italian censor (active 1575-1624): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1600 </date>(folio 357v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref>. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1618 </date>(folio 356v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Moses ben Nahman. Commentary on the Pentateuch. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Harley Ms. 5,703.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
